<subSubSection pageId="98" pageNumber="2328" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="98.[160,1155,1494,1658]" pageId="98" pageNumber="2328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,282,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="2328">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
this species group is composed of brachypterous species 
<emphasis box="[906,919,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="2328">–</emphasis>
flightless species with atrophied hindwing and is revised in Nunes and Vaz-de-Mello 2016. The group is differentiated of other by the following combined characters: anterior portion of pronotal disc with two to four lobes; hindwing atrophied (
<figureCitation box="[577,664,1599,1623]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="20.[160,225,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[166,1148,142,1488]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[163,1153,142,1490]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 7. (a) Mandible of D. fissus (Harold), inc – incisory lobe (membranous), mo – molar lobe. (b) Maxilla and maxillary palp of same species, mxp – maxillary palp, ga – galea, las – lacinia. (c) Epipharynx of same species. (d) Labrum and labial palpomere of same species. (e) Ventral clypeal process of D. fissceps indicated by white arrow.(f) Antena of same species.esc – escapo, lam – lamella. (g) Macropterous hind wig of D. fissiceps. (h) Brachypterous hindwing of D. ingens." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665533/files/figure.png" pageId="98" pageNumber="2328">Figure 7</figureCitation>
(h)); pronotum wider than elytra in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[167,268,1634,1658]" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="56.[160,225,1346,1369]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1314]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1153,142,1314]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="Figure 41. (a) D. ingens, male dorsal habitus. (b) D. darwini, male paratype dorsal habitus; (c) D. paresi, male paratype dorsal view; (d) D. manni, male holotype dorsal view. (e) D. periotoi, male, paratype dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665597/files/figure.png" pageId="98" pageNumber="2328">Figure 41</figureCitation>
); elytra strongly convex in lateral view and elytra lacking humeral callus.
</paragraph>
